+    "overview": "FT Partners is the defining specialist franchise in fintech investment banking: founder-owned since 2002, sell-side only, inbound-driven, and priced at a premium the rest of Wall Street considers audacious. The verified economics are exceptional, roughly $600M of revenue on 225 people in 2021 per the WSJ, and the moat components (proprietary dataset, research franchise, twenty-year track record) are real and compounding. The franchise nonetheless concentrates to a degree unusual even for boutiques: one owner, one brand, one fee philosophy, and a mandate book the founder still personally touches. The market it serves has passed through a 60% peak-to-trough reset and is recovering with fewer, larger deals and a reopened IPO window, conditions that favor exactly this firm, if it holds its people and its founder.",
