-  "executive_summary": {
-    "overview": "FTMO leads modern prop trading and performs remarkably on the numbers. FY2024 revenue reached about $329 million, up 53%, with net profit of about $62.5 million at a 19% margin, on a staff cost base of roughly 2.3% of revenue, about one-tenth the proportion IG Group and CMC Markets carry. FTMO grew 53% in a year when dozens of its competitors went under. Judged on the financials alone, the business looks superb. The financials are not the finding. What produces them is. FTMO earns most of its revenue from traders who fail their evaluations and forfeit non-refundable fees. The margin is extraordinary because the business is unregulated: no compliance staff, no regulatory capital, no trade reporting, no execution. That position rests entirely on the argument that the trading is simulated, an argument regulators have not yet tested. The industry lobbying for its own regulation suggests insiders expect them to.",
